WEBVTT

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:44.300
"Unfold"

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:47.500
(Episode 2)

00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:00.259
(From Dad: January 28, Mingyue Pavilion,
Hexi District, No. 366, Building 3, Room 702)

00:02:09.333 --> 00:02:10.625
Why did you come so early today?

00:02:12.583 --> 00:02:13.583
Still spacing out?

00:02:15.777 --> 00:02:16.777
No.

00:02:17.236 --> 00:02:18.410
I'm thinking about something.

00:02:20.375 --> 00:02:21.375
Where's the boss?

00:02:22.791 --> 00:02:23.833
He...

00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:27.791
He passed away yesterday.

00:02:45.208 --> 00:02:46.166
A'Che.

00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:47.166
My condolences.

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:49.910
If there's anything I can help with,
just let me know.

00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:51.708
What's happening
now at the bookstore,

00:02:51.708 --> 00:02:53.041
just leave it to me.

00:03:06.541 --> 00:03:07.625
Auntie, let me explain to you.

00:03:07.625 --> 00:03:08.665
You don't have to explain.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:10.040
You don't have to explain.

00:03:10.291 --> 00:03:11.708
Did you do it or not?

00:03:11.708 --> 00:03:13.000
Auntie, let me explain to you properly.

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.000
Stop it, you bunch of liars.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:15.541
Auntie.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:17.250
You are such a liar.

00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:19.166
How much money did you give my daughter-in-law?

00:03:19.166 --> 00:03:20.458
Letting my son die without
leaving his body intact.

00:03:20.458 --> 00:03:21.166
Auntie.

00:03:21.416 --> 00:03:22.416
How could he do it?

00:03:22.559 --> 00:03:23.851
You're a bunch of bastards.

00:03:23.875 --> 00:03:25.083
I won't let you off.

00:03:40.208 --> 00:03:41.333
I live nearby.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:43.666
Come up and change your clothes.

00:03:50.708 --> 00:03:51.750
Let me buy you a drink,

00:03:53.291 --> 00:03:55.982
just treat it as thanks you
for your generous help.

00:04:11.833 --> 00:04:12.416
You see,

00:04:12.666 --> 00:04:14.125
that ahead is my house,

00:04:15.500 --> 00:04:17.100
then make a turn here and you'll arrive.

00:04:22.125 --> 00:04:23.125
I live alone,

00:04:23.125 --> 00:04:24.125
the house is a bit messy.

00:04:24.208 --> 00:04:25.208
Please don't mind it.

00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:37.375
Or maybe,

00:04:37.375 --> 00:04:38.625
take a shower first.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:41.791
It's nothing.

00:04:41.791 --> 00:04:43.208
I don't often stay in this room,

00:04:43.208 --> 00:04:44.448
just treat it as your own home,

00:04:52.333 --> 00:04:53.750
the restroom is inside.

00:04:53.833 --> 00:04:55.125
I'll go make something first.

00:05:20.583 --> 00:05:21.916
Let's blow-dry your hair first.

00:05:30.916 --> 00:05:31.750
Wait a moment.

00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:32.750
There's another dish.

00:06:15.041 --> 00:06:15.416
Come on.

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:16.500
Thank you.

00:06:19.333 --> 00:06:21.125
Do you often cook?

00:06:22.416 --> 00:06:24.208
I do it myself when I'm not busy.

00:06:25.375 --> 00:06:26.625
Are you usually busy?

00:06:28.083 --> 00:06:30.483
There's no such thing as not being busy
in our line of work.

00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:32.708
Just now,

00:06:32.708 --> 00:06:33.833
what was happening?

00:06:35.625 --> 00:06:36.541
That was an accident.

00:06:36.541 --> 00:06:38.607
If I were beaten every day,
I wouldn't be able to take it.

00:06:42.791 --> 00:06:43.791
Are you okay?

00:06:46.291 --> 00:06:47.291
It's nothing.

00:06:54.208 --> 00:06:55.291
Thank you.

00:07:13.527 --> 00:07:14.527
How about the food?

00:07:14.958 --> 00:07:16.318
I didn't put too much salt, did I?

00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:50.416
Thank you.

00:07:50.500 --> 00:07:51.500
Come on.

00:07:57.083 --> 00:07:58.083
What's wrong?

00:08:00.125 --> 00:08:01.208
That old lady

00:08:01.208 --> 00:08:02.666
really packs a punch.

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:05.500
Wait a sec.

00:08:16.500 --> 00:08:16.958
It's nothing.

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:18.000
I can do it myself.

00:08:18.375 --> 00:08:19.625
I can handle it well.

00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:21.976
What is the appropriate degree or measure?

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:23.208
How much salt to put?

00:08:24.458 --> 00:08:25.833
I'll do it then.

00:08:30.333 --> 00:08:31.333
Don't move.

00:08:47.625 --> 00:08:48.705
Where should I throw this?

00:08:50.666 --> 00:08:51.666
Over there.

00:09:02.708 --> 00:09:04.828
This is the liver source coordinate
with your father.

00:09:05.041 --> 00:09:06.291
I thought it was over,

00:09:06.416 --> 00:09:08.791
so I didn't expect Minhua
Hospital to contact us on their own.

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:13.875
Unfortunately, I wasn't
able to help much.

00:09:15.416 --> 00:09:16.416
How could you?

00:09:21.500 --> 00:09:22.708
Has the surgery time been set?

00:09:24.041 --> 00:09:25.934
The family members hope for
an operation as soon as possible.

00:09:25.958 --> 00:09:27.625
The child's mother cries every day.

00:09:28.666 --> 00:09:29.666
Her father,

00:09:33.125 --> 00:09:34.125
What?

00:09:34.351 --> 00:09:36.583
I saw the child's father at the hospital that day.

00:09:37.291 --> 00:09:38.041
Before the 22nd,

00:09:38.041 --> 00:09:39.881
I will definitely transfer the balance to you.

00:09:40.833 --> 00:09:41.833
Rest assured.

00:09:42.375 --> 00:09:44.208
I won't take the child's life lightly,

00:09:45.958 --> 00:09:46.958
Understood.

00:09:48.041 --> 00:09:49.000
In principle,

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:52.010
the donor and recipient should not
have any information about each other.

00:09:52.791 --> 00:09:55.791
It is even more impossible to know
the hospital where the donor is located.

00:09:59.208 --> 00:10:03.000
Actually, a text message was
sent to my dad's phon yesterday.

00:10:07.541 --> 00:10:08.791
I think,

00:10:09.166 --> 00:10:11.250
He may be involved in
the illegal organ trade.

00:10:14.534 --> 00:10:16.854
The process of organ
transplantation is extremely complex.

00:10:17.333 --> 00:10:18.851
Even if we disregard
the intermediate process,

00:10:18.875 --> 00:10:19.916
even in blood type matching,

00:10:19.916 --> 00:10:21.156
it's also difficult to operate.

00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:22.958
Even if he can find an organ source,

00:10:23.625 --> 00:10:26.107
how could he ensure the organ
would match the receipient exactly?

00:10:27.618 --> 00:10:28.868
Unless...

00:10:30.449 --> 00:10:31.449
Unless what?

00:10:35.708 --> 00:10:38.041
Unless he clearly knows
the patient's blood type.

00:10:38.250 --> 00:10:39.791
Then, he'd go and look for a donor.

00:10:42.916 --> 00:10:44.291
But how can that be possible?

00:10:47.791 --> 00:10:48.375
It's getting late.

00:10:48.625 --> 00:10:49.750
Let me take you home first.

00:10:50.291 --> 00:10:51.291
Okay.

00:10:51.333 --> 00:10:52.333
Thank you.

00:11:14.583 --> 00:11:15.583
And,

00:11:16.166 --> 00:11:17.416
My home is right here.

00:11:18.250 --> 00:11:19.250
You go back first.

00:11:20.416 --> 00:11:21.656
I think you should go up first.

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:24.166
You go back first.

00:12:45.916 --> 00:12:46.916
I'll go back first then.

00:12:47.833 --> 00:12:48.833
Then I'll go.

00:12:54.250 --> 00:12:55.250
Bye-bye.

00:12:55.458 --> 00:12:56.458
Bye-bye.